name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
notes:
***1ST AND 2ND DOSE ONLY MODERNA VACCINATIONS*** !!!!VACUNAS DE SEGUNDA DOSIS ÚNICAMENTE MODERNA!!! Enter fairgrounds through Gate 12 off of Pacific Avenue. Be prepared to show confirmation of your appointment or you may experience a slightly longer wait. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. Ingresar por la puerta 12 en la avenida Pacífico. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. ***THOSE WHO GET THEIR 1ST MODERNA SHOT WILL NEED TO FIND OTHER ARRANGEMENTS TO RECEIVE THEIR SECOND DOSE BY FINDING A CLINIC AT THE WEBSITE PROVIDED. 
AQUELLOS QUE RECIBAN SU PRIMERA DISPARO MODERNA DEBERÁN ENCONTRAR OTROS ARREGLOS PARA RECIBIR SU 2ª DOSIS ENCONTRANDO UNA CLÍNICA EN EL SITIO WEB PROPORCIONADO.**** https://prepmod.doh.wa.gov/
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Yakama Nation - Yakama Cultural Center - White Swan Health Clinic Mobile COVID-19 Vaccination Site
notes:
Yakama Nation White Swan Health Clinic in association with Yakima Valley Emergency Management is hosting:

Drive-Thru Pfizer Covid-19 Clinic at the Yakama Nation Cultural Center. 

First and second doses available.

Open to the public, for anyone age 16 and over.

Pending FDA approval (yet to be approved), patients aged 12-15 will be eligible for vaccination as well.

Parents/Guardians of patients <18 years of age will be asked to sign a paper consent form, and if not physically present, will be contacted via telephone to verbally confirm consent to vaccination.

Please contact the White Swan Health Clinic with questions (509) 865-8703 or (509) 945-4612
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine - COVID Vaccine Clinic
notes:
***We provide 1st and 2nd doses of MODERNA***
Please sign up for an appointment time.  

When you arrive to the clinic, please continue to wear your face covering, practice physical distancing and wash your hands frequently to help reduce transmission.

Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. 
Expect to stay for 15 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. 

Due to the limited supplies of vaccines provided to us each week, we are unable to take walk-ins, so please make an appointment. 

***Directions to the Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine:***
Our clinic is located in the Hidden Valley Office Complex.
1) When you arrive at the complex, take either driveway all the way to the back of the building.
2) We are located on the prominent corner at the very back of the building and we have our own private entrance.  Look for the parking lot with the number "2" in a big steel frame.  Do NOT go into the main building for we have a private entrance accessible directly from the parking lot. 
Look for our sign with our logo in the window and a door with the number "C-102" on it, visible from the parking lot.
***Visit our website for further contact information and directions to the clinic: https://www.hawkerhealth.com/contact-us/ ***
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
